WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.880
[Unknown]: Everything that is happening now has happened before.

00:00:08.880 --> 00:00:12.960
[Amit Varma]: A pandemic has struck India, there has been panic, there have been heated debates about

00:00:12.960 --> 00:00:16.200
[Amit Varma]: lockdowns, about masks, about vaccines.

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:19.600
[Amit Varma]: The state has been negligent and the state has overreached.

00:00:19.600 --> 00:00:24.400
[Amit Varma]: Civil society has risen up in protest, all kinds of rumours about the disease have spread

00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:27.280
[Amit Varma]: through the land and the bodies of the dead have piled up.

00:00:27.280 --> 00:00:32.480
[Amit Varma]: Except, wait a minute, all this has not only happened before, but it has been much worse.

00:00:32.480 --> 00:00:38.280
[Amit Varma]: Between 1817 and 1920, India was struck by three pandemics, which at one point were upon

00:00:38.280 --> 00:00:39.600
[Amit Varma]: us at the same time.

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:45.000
[Amit Varma]: Cholera, the plague and influenza killed 40 million people during these 100 years.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:48.920
[Amit Varma]: In fact, 70 million if you count the 30 million killed by cholera in the years when it was

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:51.560
[Amit Varma]: merely endemic and not a pandemic.

00:00:51.560 --> 00:00:56.880
[Amit Varma]: In this time, populations have been devastated, villages wiped out and bodies have piled up

00:00:56.880 --> 00:00:58.200
[Amit Varma]: on the streets.

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:02.320
[Amit Varma]: The state has failed and the backlash has changed our history.

00:01:02.320 --> 00:01:07.520
[Amit Varma]: And yet, when we are faced with a modern pandemic today, we have forgotten all these lessons

00:01:07.520 --> 00:01:08.560
[Amit Varma]: of the past.

00:01:08.560 --> 00:01:10.620
[Amit Varma]: But these lessons matter.

00:01:10.620 --> 00:01:15.000
[Amit Varma]: To understand these modern times, to deal with the situation in which we find ourselves

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:35.400
[Unknown]: today, we need to learn about India's tryst with pandemics.

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:36.800
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to the scene and the unseen.

00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:41.480
[Amit Varma]: My guest today is Chinmay Tumbe, author of Age of Pandemics, a marvelous new book that

00:01:41.480 --> 00:01:47.080
[Amit Varma]: looks at how the Indian subcontinent was ravaged by three pandemics in the century between

00:01:47.080 --> 00:01:49.760
[Amit Varma]: 1817 and 1920.

00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:54.360
[Amit Varma]: They took more lives than we could imagine, and they shaped our history, our economy,

00:01:54.360 --> 00:01:57.640
[Amit Varma]: our politics and our society in profound ways.

00:01:57.640 --> 00:02:02.840
[Amit Varma]: Chinmay argues that we need to build a collective memory about this past so that we can avoid

00:02:02.840 --> 00:02:05.680
[Amit Varma]: its mistakes and apply its lessons.

00:02:05.680 --> 00:02:11.000
[Amit Varma]: Age of Pandemics is a wonderful book of scholarship and analysis, which is not a surprise to me

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:16.400
[Amit Varma]: because Chinmay's previous book, India Moving, a study of migration within India, is in my

00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:21.360
[Amit Varma]: opinion one of the most underrated books written about India in the last decade.

00:02:21.360 --> 00:02:25.700
[Amit Varma]: I did an episode on that book with Chinmay about a year and a half ago, and both that

00:02:25.700 --> 00:02:29.160
[Amit Varma]: book and that episode will be linked from the show notes.

00:02:29.160 --> 00:02:32.160
[Amit Varma]: I was delighted to have him once again on the show.

00:02:32.160 --> 00:02:40.440
[Amit Varma]: But before we get to our conversation, let's take a quick commercial break.

00:02:40.440 --> 00:02:44.920
[Amit Varma]: We often think of ourselves as the masters of the universe, the one species that managed

00:02:44.920 --> 00:02:46.120
[Amit Varma]: to tame the earth.

00:02:46.120 --> 00:02:47.120
[Amit Varma]: This is nonsense.

00:02:47.120 --> 00:02:51.140
[Amit Varma]: If you look at it one way, we are puppets colonized by viruses and bacteria.

00:02:51.140 --> 00:02:54.040
[Amit Varma]: We should have had occasion to think about this in 2020.

00:02:54.040 --> 00:02:58.600
[Amit Varma]: And we certainly should learn about our past encounters with these mysterious forces.

00:02:58.600 --> 00:03:01.660
